SEC. 3. To fulfill its purposes and achieve its objectives, the Biliran Cultural Center and Museum shall:

(a) Complete musical notes and lyrics of Biliran traditional songs, ballads, and contemporary music compositions, and collect samples of musical instruments of Biliran origin, design, and creation;

(b) Acquire and display a varied range of Biliran arts and artifacts;

(c) Publish and disseminate Biliran literary works, epics, stories, and historical accounts;

(d) Compile Biliran literature, film, or audio-visual recordings pf cultural performances in music, dance, oral literature, and festival celebrations;

(e) Compile Biliran works, names of barangays, towns and other places of interests and their respective history;

(f) Gather and document Biliran religious practices and traditions, and the background and origin of Biliran fiestas and festivals;

(g) Compile photographs of and showcase by appropriate exhibits, Biliran landmarks, historical sites and scenic views;

(h) Gather specimens of archaeological findings, and collect major minerals present in Biliran, namely, gypsum, sulfur, and white clay and such other geological materials unique to Biliran;

(i) Preserve by appropriate methods samples of flora and fauna indigenous to the Province of Biliran;

(j) Conduct performances on local music, dances, arts, literary works, epics, stories, historical accounts and legends; and

(k) Carry out any other relevant and appropriate activities.
